tip.text: Good coffee, quirky vibe and the alfajor is one of the better ones I've had - not too sweet and goes great with the cappuccino.
The ribeye is delicious! Small, intimate restaurant with great service.
Definitely do the hike on Perito Moreno. It's a short easy hike on crampons, stunning views and wonderful experience.
Beautiful but ridiculously touristy. Mornings are crowded, so afternoon visit would avoid the rush. No decent restaurant in town - everything is overpriced. Still worth a visit though.
As everyone mentioned, the grilled pulpo is delicious! Smoky flavors and the texture is absolutely perfect! The picarones plaza italia is really good!
Definitely one of the best restaurants in the world. Everything was delicious - playful, creative; an explosion of flavours with every dish and great textures.
The fig baklava was a pleasant surprise. The mascarpone cuts the sweetness and the nuts add some texture.
Peking cuy was quite good. My fave were the desserts though: cocoa journey and the fig baklava was absolutely divine.

Wonderful place to stay - the eco-friendly domes are cozy (toilet needs a lil getting used to). The guides are friendly & knowledgable. Excellent tours & activities. Food is made in-house & delicious.
The tres salmones is delicious - got that crunch to balance out the raw fish. :)
Food is okay - big servings but the sticky date pudding is so yummy!

tip.text: Best waffles in the city! By far the best waffles I've ever tasted!!! 😋
Best place for fondue - great mix of cheeses! But I have to say, the raclette is to die for.
Strawberry guimauve macarons if they're available!!! Fleur d'oranger is always a nice choice - something different but delish. Food wise, the salmon + avo + egg is quite good.
Homemade caramel is always good but the orange + grand marnier is a new favourite.
Everything is SOOO good! For something light, get the passion fruit + framboise.
Za'atar labne! 😋
The dark roc's with almond and orange is delish! The bouchées doubles are also good!
Crema di Fina is a must try! Cream + saffron + pine nuts. 👌🏽
the non-dairy red velvet is amazing! tastes just like red velvet cake... top it off with chocolate sprinkles or dark chocolate brownie bites! 👌🏽
Definitely go for the omakase! I had the nigiri tasting and it was superb! The flavours are amazing. The Hamachi Truffle is also great!
The tacos de pescado and the ceviche are both excellent!!! Flavorful and spicy. The ceviche is also quite refreshing.

The food is delicious (best lamb I've ever had, ever) and the view is breathtaking. We had lunch that came with the Sydney Seaplanes package and I'm happy to have chosen Jonah's.
Booked the seaplane tour with lunch at Jonah's as a birthday surprise. It was a memorable experience and made the day extra special.
The banana pancakes are good although not mind blowing but the macadamia nut sauce now that is a different story!
Best shave ice. The flavours are yummy and not overly sweet. Better than Matsumoto in my opinion.

The chocolate kouign amman is perfect with coffee. The regular one is nice too.
The valrhona chocolate soufflé is really nice. Not too heavy - perfect to cap off the meat-y meal.
You can't go wrong with the hibiscus doughnut. I also love the lemon poppy seed and the chocolate earl grey!
I really enjoyed the ricotta gnudi but it's quite rich and heavy. The Roquefort burger definitely lives up to the hype and the fries are great to munch on.
Rich hot chocolate and really pretty yummy pretty hand-made chocolates. Try the different award-winning flavours.
The food was good plus you get a nice view by the water. The roast lamb + sweetbreads was rich but a nice play on texture. I loved the poached rhubarb + ricotta ice cream + beetroot marshmallow.
Good for a nice dinner out. A bit more expensive than the places around but food is good. The duck confit was delish.
Perfect place for date night. Every course is a delight - and of course the helium apple makes you feel like a kid again.
